WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:18.000
NIRA v0.4 is a local-first assistant with visible offline status, local storage, and explicit side-effect approval.

00:18.000 --> 00:45.000
The real runtime reports healthy deterministic-offline mode. Chat works without pretending that a local model is running.

00:45.000 --> 01:15.000
Conversation history is local and user-controlled: search, open, pin, rename, export, and confirmed deletion.

01:15.000 --> 01:40.000
The first real tool inspects this repository while excluding virtual environments, dependencies, caches, and build output.

01:40.000 --> 02:00.000
The second tool reads bounded workspace content. An attempted path escape is rejected without reading the outside file.

02:00.000 --> 02:45.000
A coding plan reaches process execution and pauses. Denial is the safe default, stops the task, and is never auto-retried.

02:45.000 --> 03:00.000
Permission evidence stores the tool, access class, verdict, and reason—never the raw arguments.

03:00.000 --> 03:30.000
A second verification is approved once. The narrow compile command runs through the same registry and permission boundary.

03:30.000 --> 03:48.000
Release evidence: 49 tests, clean dependency and secret scans, and a wheel verified outside the source tree.

03:48.000 --> 04:05.000
Honest limitation: no real model profile, optional voice and PyQt outside core, and retrieval/accessibility evaluation still pending.
